  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Risk-informed Early Action Partnership</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The concept of the Risk-informed Early Action Partnership (REAP) is to bring together major players in the spheres of climate, disaster risk reduction and humanitarian action to leverage increased financial commitments and improve the way money is spent in order to widen the reach and ensure it is benefiting the&#xC2;&#xA0;people most vulnerable to a changing climate and extreme weather events. The REAP will aggregate and monitor targets along the spectrum of national and global frameworks, early warning systems, impact-based forecasting and domestic capacity building to enhance planning and delivery of early action.</narrative>
  </description>
